Interventions for preventing and treating stress fractures and stress reactions of bone of the lower limbs in young adults Stress fractures are a type of overuse injury.
They can be very painful and debilitating.
Lower limb stress fractures are common in people undergoing military training and in athletes, particularly long distance runners.
Measures to prevent stress fractures include modifications to footwear and changes to training schedules.
We found some evidence that shock absorbing boot inserts help prevent stress fractures during military training.
It is not clear what is the best design to use.
Treatment of stress fractures generally involves a long period of activity restriction.
We found some evidence that pneumatic braces may speed recovery of tibial stress fracture.